{
  "id": "019ceb20-fa13-7183-941b-8836c6db633f",
  "content": "# Claude Session History — Design Decisions\n\n## What it is\nA personal conversation recording system for Claude Code sessions. Every session is captured as structured JSONL logs, ingested into a dedicated corvia scope (`user-history`), and made searchable across sessions. Independent from product knowledge — deletable on its own lifecycle.\n\n## Architecture (Approach A — Pure Adapter)\n- **Hooks** (dumb recorders): UserPromptSubmit, PreToolUse, PostToolUse, SessionEnd → append events to `~/.claude/sessions/<session-id>.jsonl`\n- **SessionEnd**: gzips the file, triggers `corvia workspace ingest`\n- **`corvia-adapter-claude-sessions`**: reads `~/.claude/sessions/*.jsonl.gz`, chunks into one KnowledgeEntry per turn, classifies, writes to `user-history` scope\n- **Auto-discovery**: heuristic (path-based) + LLM classifier promotes product-relevant entries to `corvia` scope\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n- **User-global logs**: `~/.claude/sessions/` — not per-workspace (sessions may not be product-related)\n- **Same corvia instance, separate scope**: `scope_id: \"user-history\"` declared in `corvia.toml`; deletion via `delete_scope` + `corvia rebuild`\n- **Turn-level chunking**: one KnowledgeEntry per conversation turn (not per event) — ~7× fewer entries, keeps HNSW manageable\n- **Full fidelity + gzip**: full tool outputs recorded, gzip achieves 70–85% compression\n- **Classification state**: `.classify-queue` file (newline-delimited entry IDs) — NOT embedded in `source_origin` to preserve exact-match filter semantics\n- **Workstream = git branch**: detected at SessionStart via `git rev-parse --abbrev-ref HEAD`\n\n## Multi-Agent Support\n- Each Claude Code process → unique session_id → separate JSONL file (no concurrency issues)\n- Edge direction: `subagent_turn → \"spawned_by\" → parent_turn`\n- Find subagents: `traverse(start=parent_turn_id, relation=\"spawned_by\", direction=Incoming, depth=3)`\n- Subagent research entries: `content_role: \"research\"` — retained independently of parent session\n\n## Kernel Prerequisites\n1. **`SourceMetadata` extension** (`chunking_strategy.rs`): add `workstream`, `content_role`, `source_origin` as `Option<String>` with `#[serde(default)]`\n2. **Propagation**: update `crates/corvia-cli/src/workspace.rs` and `main.rs` (NOT ChunkingPipeline — it never constructs KnowledgeEntry)\n3. **Workstream filter**: add `workstream: Option<String>` to `RetrievalOpts`, extend `post_filter_metadata` in `retriever.rs` (3 call sites + 4 existing test call sites need `None`), thread through `rest.rs` SearchRequest and `mcp.rs` corvia_search schema\n\n## HNSW Performance Note\nLiteStore HNSW is global (not per-scope). Scope filtering is post-filter. At turn-level chunking + 6-month TTL, steady-state user-history ≈ 3,600 entries (~2× product scope) — manageable. Full deletion: `delete_scope` + `corvia rebuild` to compact.\n\n## Deliverables (ordered)\n1. SourceMetadata extension + CLI propagation PR (`corvia-kernel` + `corvia-cli`)\n2. Workstream filter PR (`corvia-kernel` + `corvia-server`)\n3. 5 hook scripts + settings.json (workspace)\n4. `corvia-adapter-claude-sessions` crate (new adapter)\n5. `corvia.toml` user-history scope entry (config)\n6. Claude Code hook env var names spike (research)\n\n## Spec location\n`repos/corvia/docs/rfcs/2026-03-14-claude-session-history-design.md`",
